news.title: Mysuru civic body submits proposal to upgrade as grade 1 city corporation
news.para: The Mysuru City Corporation (MCC) has proposed an upgrade to a grade 1 city corporation, similar to Hubballi-Dharwad, after the Greater Mysuru plan was shelved due to population constraints. This proposal involves merging surrounding municipal councils and town panchayats.

news.title: Slums gone, Chandigarh administration gets rolling with new urban blueprint
news.para: Chandigarh administration has reclaimed nearly 50 acres of government land. This land was previously occupied by slums and unauthorized structures. The administration demolished Sanjay Colony, Janta Colony and Adarsh Colony. The reclaimed land will be used for industrial plots, residential areas, and green belts.

news.title: NGT orders probe into ‘illegal’ sand mining in Dhenkanal
news.para: The National Green Tribunal has ordered a probe into alleged illegal sand mining in the Brahmani river in Dhenkanal district, following a petition by an NGO. The tribunal constituted a committee to investigate violations of environmental norms, including exceeding extraction limits and operating without proper clearances. The committee must submit a report within three weeks.

news.title: Pune & Khadki cantonment residents seek clarity on FSI after merger approval with PMC
news.para: Following the state government's approval to merge Pune and Khadki cantonment areas into the Pune Municipal Corporation, residents and activists are seeking clarity on future floor space index (FSI) regulations.

news.title: No OC for 18 floors, Bombay HC orders ‘selfish’ residents to vacate in two weeks
news.para: Bombay High Court orders residents of Willingdon Heights' upper floors to vacate within two weeks. The court criticizes their occupation without an Occupation Certificate. It highlights safety concerns and disregard for regulations. The court dismisses requests for extended stay. BMC is instructed to take action if the order is not followed. Hearing for lower floor occupants is scheduled.

news.title: Hi-tech monitoring falls flat in Ahmedabad as no builder fined for air pollution
news.para: Ahmedabad's civic body is struggling to enforce anti-pollution measures at construction sites despite advanced monitoring. Air quality sensors are mandated, but no penalties have been issued based on sensor data. The AMC is addressing pollution from Ready Mix Concrete plants and has implemented various green initiatives, earning a substantial incentive grant for air quality improvements.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government tweaks property valuation
news.para: Tamil Nadu government has revised stamp duty rules. The new rules introduce composite value for apartments. This includes the super built-up area and land share. Guideline values can now be revised anytime. Earlier revisions were only in October.

news.title: Brigade Hotel Ventures' ₹750-crore IPO to open on July 24
news.para: Brigade Hotel Ventures, a South India hotel owner, will launch its IPO on July 24. The IPO aims to raise Rs 749.6 crore. It will close on July 28. Anchor investor bidding opens on July 23. Funds will be used for debt payment and land purchase. The company has nine operating hotels across multiple cities.

news.title: NCLT approves merger of Adani Cementation with Ambuja Cements
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has approved the merger of Adani Cementation with Ambuja Cements, consolidating Adani Group's cement business. This strategic move, effective April 1, 2024, involves a share-swapping arrangement and aims to enhance value, improve resource utilization, and expand manufacturing capacity, targeting 140 MTPA by FY28.

news.title: Kalpataru pre-sales jump 41% to ₹4,531 crore in FY25
news.para: Kalpataru Limited sees a 41 percent rise in pre-sales, reaching Rs 4,531 crore. The company launched seven new projects covering 6.5 million square feet. Development agreements were signed for society redevelopment projects valued at Rs 2,100 crore. Net profit stood at Rs 21.62 crore, a significant turnaround. An IPO raised Rs 1,590 crore, used partly for debt reduction.

news.title: Mohali district earns ₹11.43 crore in property tax in just 19 days under OTS scheme
news.para: Mohali district's urban local bodies achieved a significant milestone. They collected Rs 11.43 crore in property taxes within 19 days. This happened under the one-time settlement scheme. Zirakpur led the collections. The scheme offers waivers on penalties and interest. The administration extended office hours to facilitate payments. Officials encourage residents to clear dues promptly. This avoids future penalties.

news.title: Housing societies in dilemma over NA tax in absence of Maharashtra government resolution
news.para: Confusion persists among Maharashtra's urban housing societies regarding the abolition of non-agricultural (NA) tax, despite a cabinet announcement ten months prior. The absence of a formal government resolution (GR) has left societies uncertain about continuing payments. While the government acknowledges the delay due to elections, a GR is expected soon to provide clarity and directives to resolve the ongoing dilemma.

news.title: JSW Paints seeks CCI nod to acquire majority stake in Akzo Nobel India for ₹12,915 crore
news.para: JSW Paints is set to acquire a majority stake in Akzo Nobel India for ₹12,915 crore, pending CCI approval. This move will make JSW Paints the fourth-largest player in the Indian paint industry. The deal involves purchasing a 74.76% stake initially, followed by an open offer for an additional 25%.

news.title: Indiramma housing stalled after Centre's missive to Telangana
news.para: Telangana's Indiramma housing scheme faces hurdles as the Union housing ministry finds its proposals non-compliant with PMAY norms. The ministry demands live facial authentication via Aadhaar for 19.5 lakh rural beneficiaries by July 31. Despite this, the state government is confident in meeting the deadline.

news.title: Karnataka govt to levy groundwater extraction charges; meters now mandatory for all users
news.para: Karnataka is implementing groundwater usage charges, ranging from Re 1 to Rs 35 per cubic meter, for various users, including individuals, societies, and industries. Mandatory NOCs are required for borewells, with extraction caps for tankers based on zone criticality. Revenue generated will fund recharge initiatives, promoting sustainable water resource management across the state.

news.title: All 380 registration offices to have own buildings: Uttar Pradesh minister
news.para: UP Minister Ravindra Jaiswal announced that all 380 registration offices in Uttar Pradesh will have their own buildings with modern facilities. He inaugurated and laid the foundation for eight registration office buildings costing Rs 18.56 crore. The initiative aims to provide better facilities to the public, with hi-tech offices equipped with solar energy and water harvesting provisions.

news.title: Building bylaws revised, Ghaziabad development body halts map approvals till September
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority halts online map approvals until September. This is to incorporate the UP Building Construction Bylaws, 2025. Approvals will now be manual, potentially extending the process to a month. Officials anticipate temporary inconvenience and revenue impact.

news.title: Kochi: Construction of new houses for Shanthipuram Colony residents begins
news.para: The Kochi corporation has initiated the reconstruction of houses for 197 families in Shanthipuram Colony, Karanakodam, utilizing Life Mission funds and CSR contributions. The project aims to replace dilapidated houses with apartment complexes, each housing eight families, with construction costs estimated at Rs 10 lakh per house.

news.title: Sand shortage hits real estate, government infrastructure projects across Jharkhand
news.para: Jharkhand faces a sand crisis due to the National Green Tribunal's monsoon ban on sand mining, halting construction projects and inflating prices. Infrastructure development is stalled, and real estate projects are delayed, frustrating investors. Businesses are now sourcing sand from Bihar at significantly higher costs, with prices increasing by Rs 10,000-15,000 per truck.

news.title: Telangana RERA slaps penalty on realty firm for layout violations in Mokila
news.para: TGRERA has penalized a realty firm Rs 38.5 lakh for violations and deviations in a Westend Greens villa project. The builder failed to deliver possession-ready units despite collecting full payments, prompting residents to file a complaint. TGRERA has directed the firm to halt sales until RERA registration and address infrastructure issues, including sewage disposal and incomplete construction.
